# BlackBar Speculative Execution Architecture

> Branch prediction for expert report pipelines.
> Predict → Execute → Validate → Promote or Discard.

---

## What It Is

After each agent stage completes, BlackBar predicts the most likely human action (approve) and speculatively executes the next stage before the human acts. Results live in an overlay — invisible to the user until promoted.

When Lane approves: the next stage is already done. Instant transition.
When Lane revises: speculative output is discarded, stage re-runs with feedback.
When Lane rejects: speculative output is discarded, pipeline halts.

This is CPU branch prediction applied to an AI agent pipeline.

## Three-System Pipeline

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                             │
│   SPECULATION ENGINE (speculation.ts)                       │
│   ─────────────────────────────────                         │
│   After stage N completes:                                  │
│   1. Check acceptance rate for stage N (>70% → speculate)   │
│   2. Fork background agent call for stage N+1               │
│   3. Use fast model (Sonnet) — cheap, aggressive            │
│   4. Store result in overlay (never visible to user)        │
│   5. On completion → hand off to Advisor                    │
│                                                             │
│   ADVISOR GATE (advisor.ts)                                 │
│   ─────────────────────────                                 │
│   Validates speculative output with smart model (Opus):     │
│   1. Voice compliance — does it sound like Lane?            │
│   2. Legal safety — no prohibited terms, no FRE 407?        │
│   3. Factual accuracy — citations correct?                  │
│   4. Structural integrity — right format?                   │
│   Score < 80 → discard speculation before human sees it     │
│   Score >= 80 → mark as validated, ready for promotion      │
│                                                             │
│   MEASUREMENT FRAMEWORK (pipelineMetrics.ts)                │
│   ─────────────────────────────────────                     │
│   Records everything:                                       │
│   - Prediction accuracy (promoted vs discarded)             │
│   - Time saved per promoted speculation                     │
│   - Advisor effectiveness (false positives/negatives)       │
│   - Cost: speculative spend vs real spend                   │
│   - Chain depth (how many stages ahead did we get?)         │
│   Every case generates training signal for the system.      │
│   Acceptance rates improve → speculation gets more          │
│   aggressive → pipeline gets faster.                        │
│                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Execution Flow

```
Case: Gleason — Initial Report — Slip & Fall

INTAKE AGENT completes (4.2s)
  ├── Result: intake.md posted to case folder
  ├── SSE: "Intake complete — case classified"
  ├── HumanCheckpoint shown to Lane
  │
  │   [BACKGROUND: Speculation engine activates]
  │   ├── Acceptance rate for intake: 92% → SPECULATE
  │   ├── Fork: Research Agent (Sonnet, speculative=true)
  │   │   ├── Reads intake.md + BRAIN §6,8,9,10
  │   │   ├── Scans for attack patterns
  │   │   └── Produces: research.md (speculative)
  │   ├── Advisor (Opus) validates research.md
  │   │   ├── Attack patterns valid? ✓ (88/100)
  │   │   ├── Citations correct? ✓ (92/100)
  │   │   ├── Completeness? ✓ (85/100)
  │   │   └── Overall: 88/100 → VALIDATED
  │   └── Status: speculation ready for promotion
  │
  │   [Meanwhile, Lane is reviewing intake results...]
  │
  └── Lane clicks APPROVE (45 seconds later)
      ├── resolveSpeculation() called
      ├── Speculation status: validated (88/100)
      ├── PROMOTED — research.md becomes the real result
      ├── SSE: "Research pre-computed — saved 12.3s"
      ├── Case advances to Research stage (already complete!)
      │
      │   [BACKGROUND: Speculation chains forward]
      │   ├── Acceptance rate for research: 78% → SPECULATE
      │   ├── Fork: Drafting Agent (Sonnet, speculative)
      │   └── ... (same pattern)
      │
      └── Lane sees Research findings immediately
          No wait. No spinner. Instant.

  ─── If Lane had clicked REVISE instead: ───
      ├── resolveSpeculation() called with action='revise'
      ├── Speculation DISCARDED
      ├── Research Agent re-runs with Lane's feedback notes
      └── New speculation starts after the revised research completes
```

## Model Strategy

| Role | Model | Why |
|------|-------|-----|
| Speculation (generation) | `claude-sonnet-4-6` | Cheap ($3/$15 per M tokens), fast (~3s per stage), good enough for 80% of cases |
| Advisor (validation) | `claude-opus-4-6` | Expensive ($15/$75 per M tokens), but only runs once per speculation — catches voice drift, legal risk, citation errors |
| Fallback (on revision) | `claude-opus-4-6` | When speculation is wrong and Lane revises, the re-run uses Opus directly — accuracy matters more than speed after a failed prediction |

**Cost math per case (4 stages, typical flow):**

| Scenario | Sonnet Calls | Opus Calls | Est. Cost |
|----------|-------------|-----------|-----------|
| No speculation | 0 | 4 (one per stage) | ~$0.60 |
| Speculation, 100% promoted | 4 (speculative) + 4 (advisor) | 4 (advisor) | ~$0.72 |
| Speculation, 75% promoted | 4 (speculative) + 4 (advisor) + 1 (re-run) | 5 | ~$0.80 |

Speculation adds ~$0.12-0.20 per case in exchange for eliminating wait time between stages. At Lane's billing rate, the time saved on a single case pays for months of API costs.

## Configuration

```env
# Enable/disable speculation
SPECULATION_ENABLED=true

# Model selection
SPECULATION_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
ADVISOR_MODEL=claude-opus-4-6

# Minimum acceptance rate to trigger speculation (0.0-1.0)
SPECULATION_MIN_ACCEPTANCE=0.7

# Advisor validation threshold (0-100)
ADVISOR_THRESHOLD=80

# Timeout: discard speculation after N minutes of no human action
SPECULATION_TIMEOUT_MINUTES=30

# Stages where speculation pauses (comma-separated)
# e.g., if Lane always revises drafts, pause before qa
SPECULATION_PAUSE_STAGES=

# Max speculation depth (how many stages ahead)
SPECULATION_MAX_DEPTH=2
```

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `server/services/speculation.ts` | Core engine — predict, execute, promote/discard |
| `server/services/advisor.ts` | Dual-model validation gate |
| `server/services/pipelineMetrics.ts` | Measurement framework — tracks everything |
| `server/routes/agents.ts` | Wired in: approve endpoint resolves speculation |

## Self-Improving Loop

The system gets better automatically:

1. **Acceptance rates update per stage.** If Lane always approves intake but frequently revises drafting, speculation becomes aggressive on intake and conservative on drafting.

2. **Advisor threshold tunes itself.** If the advisor passes speculations that Lane revises, the threshold goes up. If the advisor rejects speculations that Lane would have approved, the threshold goes down. [FUTURE: automatic threshold adjustment]

3. **Model selection adapts.** If Sonnet speculation accuracy drops below 60% for a stage, that stage switches to Opus for speculation — slower but more accurate. [FUTURE: per-stage model routing]

4. **Cost tracking prevents runaway.** If speculative spend exceeds 30% of total API cost with low promotion rates, speculation auto-disables for that stage. [FUTURE: budget kill switch]

Every case Lane runs through BlackBar generates signal that makes the next case faster.

